        "created_at": "2017-07-10T14:17:49.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thanks for the notes, Tim.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Tim Heaton\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Tim Heaton:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>(Note: <em>I read this morning that this wine got 100 points. Hogwash. 100 points is about the person doing the awarding/anointing, not the wine; wines need scores like bears need bicycles.  This wine would, normally, receive a + sign after its VHR (very highly recommended), but it\u2019s no longer an exceptional value relative to its peers, <strong>thanks to a very small group of people, none of which actually worked in Monvigliero vineyard</strong></em>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I don\u2019t understand the bolded phrase.</p>",
